{"copyright": {"licenseType": "NO", "determinationType": "GOV_PUBLIC_USE_PERMITTED", "thirdPartyContentCondition": "NOT_SET"}, "subjectCategories": ["COMMUNICATIONS AND RADAR"], "exportControl": {"isExportControl": "NO", "ear": "NO", "itar": "NO"}, "created": "2013-09-06T17:38:00.0000000+00:00", "distributionDate": "2013-08-27T00:00:00.0000000+00:00", "center": {"code": "CDMS", "name": "Legacy CDMS", "id": "092d6e0881874968859b972d39a888dc"}, "onlyAbstract": false, "sensitiveInformation": 2, "abstract": "Design considerations are discussed for Low Earth Orbit (LEO) satellite based telecommunications networks. The satellites are assumed to be connected to each other via intersatellite links. They are connected to the end user either directly or through gateways to other networks. Frequency reuse, circuit switching, packet switching, call handoff, and routing for these systems are discussed by analogy with terrestrial cellular (mobile radio) telecommunication systems.", "title": "Leo satellite-based telecommunication network concepts", "stiType": "CONFERENCE_PAPER", "distribution": "PUBLIC", "submittedDate": "2013-09-06T17:38:00.0000000+00:00", "isLessonsLearned": false, "authorAffiliations": [{"sequence": 0, "submissionId": 19920021682, "meta": {"author": {"name": "Aiken, John G."}, "organization": {"name": "Motorola, Inc.", "location": "Schaumburg, IL, United States"}}, "id": "facd42b74302444b936b6ffddf0dab49"}, {"sequence": 1, "submissionId": 19920021682, "meta": {"author": {"name": "Swan, Peter A."}, "organization": {"name": "Motorola, Inc.", "location": "Schaumburg, IL, United States"}}, "id": "d947f43221b54f6ca791657191bf6a3d"}, {"sequence": 2, "submissionId": 19920021682, "meta": {"author": {"name": "Leopold, Ray J."}, "organization": {"name": "Motorola, Inc.", "location": "Schaumburg, IL, United States"}}, "id": "6a9dc3dc1ce94156b96aedd8a6843133"}], "disseminated": "METADATA_ONLY", "stiTypeDetails": "Conference Paper", "technicalReviewType": "TECHNICAL_REVIEW_